 185// --- apm.FCtype.c_field.Remove
 186// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
 187void apm::c_field_Remove(apm::FCtype& ctype, apm::FField& row) {
 188    if (bool_Update(row.ctype_c_field_in_ary,false)) {
 189        int lim = ctype.c_field_n;
 190        apm::FField* *elems = ctype.c_field_elems;
 191        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
 192        // if found, shift array.
 193        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
 194            apm::FField* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
 195            if (elem == &row) {
 196                int j = i + 1;
 197                size_t nbytes = sizeof(apm::FField*) * (lim - j);
 198                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
 199                ctype.c_field_n = lim - 1;
 200                break;
 201            }
 202        }
 203    }
 204}

 207// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
 208void apm::c_field_Reserve(apm::FCtype& ctype, u32 n) {
 209    u32 old_max = ctype.c_field_max;
 210    if (UNLIKELY(ctype.c_field_n + n > old_max)) {
 211        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
 212        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(apm::FField*);
 213        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(apm::FField*);
 214        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(ctype.c_field_elems, old_size, new_size);
 215        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
 216            FatalErrorExit("apm.out_of_memory  field:apm.FCtype.c_field");
 217        }
 218        ctype.c_field_elems = (apm::FField**)new_mem;
 219        ctype.c_field_max = new_max;
 220    }

 308// --- apm.FDb._db.ReadArgv
 309// Read argc,argv directly into the fields of the command line(s)
 310// The following fields are updated:
 311//     apm.FDb.cmdline
 312//     algo_lib.FDb.cmdline
 313void apm::ReadArgv() {
 314    command::apm &cmd = apm::_db.cmdline;
 315    algo_lib::Cmdline &base = algo_lib::_db.cmdline;
 316    int needarg=-1;// unknown
 317    int argidx=1;// skip process name
 318    int anonidx=0;
 319    algo::strptr nextanon = command::apm_GetAnon(cmd, anonidx);
 320    tempstr err;
 321    algo::strptr attrname;
 322    bool isanon=false; // true if attrname is anonfld (positional)
 323    algo_lib::FieldId baseattrid;
 324    command::FieldId attrid;
 325    bool endopt=false;
 326    int whichns=0;// which namespace does the current attribute belong to
 327    for (; argidx < algo_lib::_db.argc; argidx++) {
 328        algo::strptr arg = algo_lib::_db.argv[argidx];
 329        algo::strptr attrval;
 330        algo::strptr dfltval;
 331        bool haveval=false;
 332        bool dash=elems_N(arg)>1 && arg.elems[0]=='-'; // a single dash is not an option
 333        // this attribute is a value
 334        if (endopt || needarg>0 || !dash) {
 335            attrval=arg;
 336            haveval=true;
 337        } else {
 338            // this attribute is a field name (with - or --)
 339            // or a -- by itself
 340            bool dashdash = elems_N(arg) >= 2 && arg.elems[1]=='-';
 341            int skip = int(dash) + dashdash;
 342            attrname=ch_RestFrom(arg,skip);
 343            if (skip==2 && elems_N(arg)==2) {
 344                endopt=true;
 345                continue;// nothing else to do here
 346            }
 347            // parse "-a:B" arg into attrname,attrvalue
 348            algo::i32_Range colon = TFind(attrname,':');
 349            if (colon.beg < colon.end) {
 350                attrval=ch_RestFrom(attrname,colon.end);
 351                attrname=ch_FirstN(attrname,colon.beg);
 352                haveval=true;
 353            }
 354            // look up which command (this one or the base) contains the field
 355            whichns=0;
 356            needarg=-1;
 357            // look up parameter information in base namespace (needarg will be -1 if lookup fails)
 358            if (algo_lib::FieldId_ReadStrptrMaybe(baseattrid,attrname)) {
 359                needarg = algo_lib::Cmdline_NArgs(baseattrid,dfltval,&isanon);
 360            }
 361            if (needarg<0) {
 362                whichns=1;
 363                // look up parameter information in this namespace (needarg will be -1 if lookup fails)
 364                if (command::FieldId_ReadStrptrMaybe(attrid,attrname)) {
 365                    needarg = command::apm_NArgs(attrid,dfltval,&isanon);
 366                }
 367            }
 368            if (attrval == "" && dfltval != "") {
 369                attrval=dfltval;
 370                haveval=true;
 371            }
 372            if (needarg<0) {
 373                err<<"apm: unknown option "<<Keyval("value",arg)<<eol;
 374            } else {
 375                if (isanon) {
 376                    if (attrname == nextanon) { // treat named anon (positional) argument as unnamed
 377                        attrname = ""; // treat it as unnamed
 378                    } else if (nextanon != "") { // disallow out-of-order anon (positional) args
 379                        err<<"apm: error at "<<algo::strptr_ToSsim(arg)<<": must be preceded by [-"<<nextanon<<"]"<<eol;
 380                    }
 381                }
 382            }
 383        }
 384        // look up anon field name based on index
 385        // anon fields are only allowed in the leaf ns, never base
 386        if (ch_N(attrname) == 0) {
 387            attrname = nextanon;
 388            nextanon = command::apm_GetAnon(cmd, ++anonidx);
 389            command::FieldId_ReadStrptrMaybe(attrid,attrname);
 390            whichns=1;
 391        }
 392        if (ch_N(attrname) == 0) {
 393            err << "apm: too many arguments. error at "<<algo::strptr_ToSsim(arg)<<eol;
 394        }
 395        // read value into currently selected arg
 396        if (haveval) {
 397            bool ret=false;
 398            // it's already known which namespace is consuming the args,
 399            // so directly go there
 400            if (whichns == 0) {
 401                ret=algo_lib::Cmdline_ReadFieldMaybe(base, attrname, attrval);
 402            }
 403            if (whichns==1) {
 404                ret=command::apm_ReadFieldMaybe(cmd, attrname, attrval);
 405                switch(attrid.value) {
 406                    default:break;
 407                }
 408            }
 409            if (!ret) {
 410                err<<"apm: error in "
 411                <<Keyval("option",attrname)
 412                <<Keyval("value",attrval)<<eol;
 413            }
 414            needarg--;
 415            if (needarg <= 0) {
 416                attrname="";// forget which argument was being filled
 417            }
 418        }
 419    }
 420    bool dohelp = false;
 421    bool doexit=false;
 422    if (algo_lib::_db.cmdline.help) {
 423        dohelp = true;
 424        doexit = true;
 425        algo_lib::_db.exit_code = 1; // help exits with non-zero status code
 426    } else if (algo_lib::_db.cmdline.version) {
 427        // -ver output goes to stdout
 428        prlog(algo::gitinfo_Get());
 429        doexit = true;
 430    } else if (algo_lib::_db.cmdline.signature) {
 431        ind_beg(algo_lib::_db_dispsigcheck_curs,dispsigcheck,algo_lib::_db) {
 432            // dispsig goes to stdout
 433            dmmeta::Dispsigcheck out;
 434            dispsigcheck_CopyOut(dispsigcheck,out);
 435            prlog(out);
 436        }ind_end
 437        doexit = true;
 438    }
 439    if (!dohelp) {
 440    }
 441    // dmmeta.floadtuples:apm.FDb.cmdline
 442    if (!dohelp && err=="") {
 443        algo_lib::ResetErrtext();
 444        if (!apm::LoadTuplesMaybe(cmd.in,true)) {
 445            err << "apm.load_input  "<<algo_lib::DetachBadTags()<<eol;
 446        }
 447    }
 448    if (err != "") {
 449        algo_lib::_db.exit_code=1;
 450        prerr(err);
 451        doexit=true;
 452    }
 453    if (dohelp) {
 454        prlog(apm_help);
 455    }
 456    if (doexit) {
 457        _exit(algo_lib::_db.exit_code);
 458    }
 459    algo_lib::ResetErrtext();
 460}

 462// --- apm.FDb._db.MainLoop
 463// Main loop.
 464void apm::MainLoop() {
 465    algo::SchedTime time(algo::get_cycles());
 466    algo_lib::_db.clock          = time;
 467    do {
 468        algo_lib::_db.next_loop.value = algo_lib::_db.limit;
 469        apm::Steps();
 470    } while (algo_lib::_db.next_loop < algo_lib::_db.limit);
 471}

 474// Main step
 475void apm::Step() {
 476}

 498// --- apm.FDb._db.InsertStrptrMaybe
 499// Parse strptr into known type and add to database.
 500// Return value is true unless an error occurs. If return value is false, algo_lib::_db.errtext has error text
 501bool apm::InsertStrptrMaybe(algo::strptr str) {
 502    bool retval = true;
 503    apm::TableId table_id(-1);
 504    value_SetStrptrMaybe(table_id, algo::GetTypeTag(str));
 505    switch (value_GetEnum(table_id)) {
 506        case apm_TableId_dev_Package: { // finput:apm.FDb.package
 507            dev::Package elem;
 508            retval = dev::Package_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
 509            retval = retval && package_InputMaybe(elem);
 510            retval = true; // finput strict:N
 511            break;
 512        }
 513        case apm_TableId_dev_Pkgkey: { // finput:apm.FDb.pkgkey
 514            dev::Pkgkey elem;
 515            retval = dev::Pkgkey_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
 516            retval = retval && pkgkey_InputMaybe(elem);
 517            retval = true; // finput strict:N
 518            break;
 519        }
 520        case apm_TableId_dev_Pkgdep: { // finput:apm.FDb.pkgdep
 521            dev::Pkgdep elem;
 522            retval = dev::Pkgdep_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
 523            retval = retval && pkgdep_InputMaybe(elem);
 524            retval = true; // finput strict:N
 525            break;
 526        }
 527        case apm_TableId_dmmeta_Ctype: { // finput:apm.FDb.ctype
 528            dmmeta::Ctype elem;
 529            retval = dmmeta::Ctype_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
 530            retval = retval && ctype_InputMaybe(elem);
 531            retval = true; // finput strict:N
 532            break;
 533        }
 534        case apm_TableId_dmmeta_Field: { // finput:apm.FDb.field
 535            dmmeta::Field elem;
 536            retval = dmmeta::Field_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
 537            retval = retval && field_InputMaybe(elem);
 538            retval = true; // finput strict:N
 539            break;
 540        }
 541        case apm_TableId_dmmeta_Ssimfile: { // finput:apm.FDb.ssimfile
 542            dmmeta::Ssimfile elem;
 543            retval = dmmeta::Ssimfile_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
 544            retval = retval && ssimfile_InputMaybe(elem);
 545            retval = true; // finput strict:N
 546            break;
 547        }
 548        case apm_TableId_dmmeta_Substr: { // finput:apm.FDb.substr
 549            dmmeta::Substr elem;
 550            retval = dmmeta::Substr_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
 551            retval = retval && substr_InputMaybe(elem);
 552            retval = true; // finput strict:N
 553            break;
 554        }
 555        case apm_TableId_dmmeta_Ssimreq: { // finput:apm.FDb.ssimreq
 556            dmmeta::Ssimreq elem;
 557            retval = dmmeta::Ssimreq_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
 558            retval = retval && ssimreq_InputMaybe(elem);
 559            retval = true; // finput strict:N
 560            break;
 561        }
 562        case apm_TableId_dmmeta_Ns: { // finput:apm.FDb.ns
 563            dmmeta::Ns elem;
 564            retval = dmmeta::Ns_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
 565            retval = retval && ns_InputMaybe(elem);
 566            retval = true; // finput strict:N
 567            break;
 568        }
 569        default:
 570        break;
 571    } //switch
 572    if (!retval) {
 573        algo_lib::NoteInsertErr(str); // increment error counter
 574    }
 575    return retval;
 576}

 578// --- apm.FDb._db.LoadTuplesMaybe
 579// Load all finputs from given directory.
 580bool apm::LoadTuplesMaybe(algo::strptr root, bool recursive) {
 581    bool retval = true;
 582    if (FileQ(root)) {
 583        retval = apm::LoadTuplesFile(root, recursive);
 584    } else if (root == "-") {
 585        retval = apm::LoadTuplesFd(algo::Fildes(0),"(stdin)",recursive);
 586    } else if (DirectoryQ(root)) {
 587        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.ns"),recursive);
 588        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.ctype"),recursive);
 589        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.field"),recursive);
 590        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.substr"),recursive);
 591        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.ssimfile"),recursive);
 592        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.ssimreq"),recursive);
 593        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.ftuple"),recursive);
 594        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.fconst"),recursive);
 595        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.dispsigcheck"),recursive);
 596        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.cppfunc"),recursive);
 597        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.cfmt"),recursive);
 598        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.cdflt"),recursive);
 599        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.unstablefld"),recursive);
 600        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.package"),recursive);
 601        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.pkgkey"),recursive);
 602        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.pkgdep"),recursive);
 603        retval = retval && apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"amcdb.bltin"),recursive);
 604    } else {
 605        algo_lib::SaveBadTag("path", root);
 606        algo_lib::SaveBadTag("comment", "Wrong working directory?");
 607        retval = false;
 608    }
 609    return retval;
 610}

 612// --- apm.FDb._db.LoadTuplesFile
 613// Load all finputs from given file.
 614// Read tuples from file FNAME into this namespace's in-memory database.
 615// If RECURSIVE is TRUE, then also load these tuples into any parent namespaces
 616// It a file referred to by FNAME is missing, no error is reported (it's considered an empty set).
 617// Function returns TRUE if all records were parsed and inserted without error.
 618// If the function returns FALSE, use algo_lib::DetachBadTags() for error description
 619bool apm::LoadTuplesFile(algo::strptr fname, bool recursive) {
 620    bool retval = true;
 621    algo_lib::FFildes fildes;
 622    // missing files are not an error
 623    fildes.fd = OpenRead(fname,algo::FileFlags());
 624    if (ValidQ(fildes.fd)) {
 625        retval = LoadTuplesFd(fildes.fd, fname, recursive);
 626    }
 627    return retval;
 628}
 629
 630// --- apm.FDb._db.LoadTuplesFd
 631// Load all finputs from given file descriptor.
 632bool apm::LoadTuplesFd(algo::Fildes fd, algo::strptr fname, bool recursive) {
 633    bool retval = true;
 634    ind_beg(algo::FileLine_curs,line,fd) {
 635        if (recursive) {
 636            retval = retval && algo_lib::InsertStrptrMaybe(line);
 637            retval = retval && lib_ctype::InsertStrptrMaybe(line);
 638        }
 639        retval = retval && apm::InsertStrptrMaybe(line);
 640        if (!retval) {
 641            algo_lib::_db.errtext << eol
 642            << fname << ":"
 643            << (ind_curs(line).i+1)
 644            << ": " << line << eol;
 645            break;
 646        }
 647    }ind_end;
 648    return retval;
 649}

 658    return retval;

 675// --- apm.FDb.package.Alloc
 676// Allocate memory for new default row.
 677// If out of memory, process is killed.
 678apm::FPackage& apm::package_Alloc() {
 679    apm::FPackage* row = package_AllocMaybe();
 680    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 681        FatalErrorExit("apm.out_of_mem  field:apm.FDb.package  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 682    }
 683    return *row;
 684}

 686// --- apm.FDb.package.AllocMaybe
 687// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 688apm::FPackage* apm::package_AllocMaybe() {
 689    apm::FPackage *row = (apm::FPackage*)package_AllocMem();
 690    if (row) {
 691        new (row) apm::FPackage; // call constructor
 692    }
 693    return row;
 694}
 695
 696// --- apm.FDb.package.InsertMaybe
 697// Create new row from struct.
 698// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 699apm::FPackage* apm::package_InsertMaybe(const dev::Package &value) {
 700    apm::FPackage *row = &package_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 701    package_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dev::Package&>(value));
 702    bool ok = package_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 703    if (!ok) {
 704        package_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 705        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 706    }
 707    return row;
 708}
 709
 710// --- apm.FDb.package.AllocMem
 711// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 712void* apm::package_AllocMem() {
 713    u64 new_nelems     = _db.package_n+1;
 714    // compute level and index on level
 715    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 716    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 717    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 718    void *ret = NULL;
 719    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 720    apm::FPackage*  lev   = NULL;
 721    if (bsr < 32) {
 722        lev = _db.package_lary[bsr];
 723        if (!lev) {
 724            lev=(apm::FPackage*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(apm::FPackage) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 725            _db.package_lary[bsr] = lev;
 726        }
 727    }
 728    // allocate element from this level
 729    if (lev) {
 730        _db.package_n = i32(new_nelems);
 731        ret = lev + index;
 732    }
 733    return ret;
 734}
 735
 736// --- apm.FDb.package.RemoveAll
 737// Remove all elements from Lary
 738void apm::package_RemoveAll() {
 739    for (u64 n = _db.package_n; n>0; ) {
 740        n--;
 741        package_qFind(u64(n)).~FPackage(); // destroy last element
 742        _db.package_n = i32(n);
 743    }
 744}
 745
 746// --- apm.FDb.package.RemoveLast
 747// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 748void apm::package_RemoveLast() {
 749    u64 n = _db.package_n;
 750    if (n > 0) {
 751        n -= 1;
 752        package_qFind(u64(n)).~FPackage();
 753        _db.package_n = i32(n);
 754    }
 755}

 764// --- apm.FDb.package.XrefMaybe
 765// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 766// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 767bool apm::package_XrefMaybe(apm::FPackage &row) {
 768    bool retval = true;
 769    (void)row;
 770    // insert package into index ind_package
 771    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 772        bool success = ind_package_InsertMaybe(row);
 773        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 774            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 775            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "apm.duplicate_key  xref:apm.FDb.ind_package"; // check for duplicate key
 776            return false;
 777        }
 778    }
 779    return retval;
 780}

 782// --- apm.FDb.zd_sel_package.Insert
 783// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
 784void apm::zd_sel_package_Insert(apm::FPackage& row) {
 785    if (!zd_sel_package_InLlistQ(row)) {
 786        apm::FPackage* old_tail = _db.zd_sel_package_tail;
 787        row.zd_sel_package_next = NULL;
 788        row.zd_sel_package_prev = old_tail;
 789        _db.zd_sel_package_tail = &row;
 790        apm::FPackage **new_row_a = &old_tail->zd_sel_package_next;
 791        apm::FPackage **new_row_b = &_db.zd_sel_package_head;
 792        apm::FPackage **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
 793        *new_row = &row;
 794        _db.zd_sel_package_n++;
 795    }
 796}
 797
 798// --- apm.FDb.zd_sel_package.Remove
 799// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
 800void apm::zd_sel_package_Remove(apm::FPackage& row) {
 801    if (zd_sel_package_InLlistQ(row)) {
 802        apm::FPackage* old_head       = _db.zd_sel_package_head;
 803        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
 804        apm::FPackage* prev = row.zd_sel_package_prev;
 805        apm::FPackage* next = row.zd_sel_package_next;
 806        // if element is first, adjust list head; otherwise, adjust previous element's next
 807        apm::FPackage **new_next_a = &prev->zd_sel_package_next;
 808        apm::FPackage **new_next_b = &_db.zd_sel_package_head;
 809        apm::FPackage **new_next = prev ? new_next_a : new_next_b;
 810        *new_next = next;
 811        // if element is last, adjust list tail; otherwise, adjust next element's prev
 812        apm::FPackage **new_prev_a = &next->zd_sel_package_prev;
 813        apm::FPackage **new_prev_b = &_db.zd_sel_package_tail;
 814        apm::FPackage **new_prev = next ? new_prev_a : new_prev_b;
 815        *new_prev = prev;
 816        _db.zd_sel_package_n--;
 817        row.zd_sel_package_next=(apm::FPackage*)-1; // not-in-list
 818    }
 819}
 820
 821// --- apm.FDb.zd_sel_package.RemoveAll
 822// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
 823void apm::zd_sel_package_RemoveAll() {
 824    apm::FPackage* row = _db.zd_sel_package_head;
 825    _db.zd_sel_package_head = NULL;
 826    _db.zd_sel_package_tail = NULL;
 827    _db.zd_sel_package_n = 0;
 828    while (row) {
 829        apm::FPackage* row_next = row->zd_sel_package_next;
 830        row->zd_sel_package_next  = (apm::FPackage*)-1;
 831        row->zd_sel_package_prev  = NULL;
 832        row = row_next;
 833    }
 834}

 836// --- apm.FDb.zd_sel_package.RemoveFirst
 837// If linked list is empty, return NULL. Otherwise unlink and return pointer to first element.
 838apm::FPackage* apm::zd_sel_package_RemoveFirst() {
 839    apm::FPackage *row = NULL;
 840    row = _db.zd_sel_package_head;
 841    if (row) {
 842        apm::FPackage *next = row->zd_sel_package_next;
 843        _db.zd_sel_package_head = next;
 844        apm::FPackage **new_end_a = &next->zd_sel_package_prev;
 845        apm::FPackage **new_end_b = &_db.zd_sel_package_tail;
 846        apm::FPackage **new_end = next ? new_end_a : new_end_b;
 847        *new_end = NULL;
 848        _db.zd_sel_package_n--;
 849        row->zd_sel_package_next = (apm::FPackage*)-1; // mark as not-in-list
 850    }
 851    return row;
 852}

 854// --- apm.FDb.ind_package.Find
 855// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 856apm::FPackage* apm::ind_package_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 857    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_package_buckets_n - 1);
 858    apm::FPackage* *e = &_db.ind_package_buckets_elems[index];
 859    apm::FPackage* ret=NULL;
 860    do {
 861        ret       = *e;
 862        bool done = !ret || (*ret).package == key;
 863        if (done) break;
 864        e         = &ret->ind_package_next;
 865    } while (true);
 866    return ret;
 867}

 869// --- apm.FDb.ind_package.FindX
 870// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
 871apm::FPackage& apm::ind_package_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
 872    apm::FPackage* ret = ind_package_Find(key);
 873    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "apm.key_error  table:ind_package  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
 874    return *ret;
 875}

 877// --- apm.FDb.ind_package.GetOrCreate
 878// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
 879apm::FPackage& apm::ind_package_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
 880    apm::FPackage* ret = ind_package_Find(key);
 881    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
 882        ret         = &package_Alloc();
 883        (*ret).package = key;
 884        bool good = package_XrefMaybe(*ret);
 885        if (!good) {
 886            package_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 887            ret = NULL;
 888        }
 889    }
 890    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "apm.create_error  table:ind_package  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
 891    return *ret;
 892}
 893
 894// --- apm.FDb.ind_package.InsertMaybe
 895// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 896bool apm::ind_package_InsertMaybe(apm::FPackage& row) {
 897    ind_package_Reserve(1);
 898    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 899    if (LIKELY(row.ind_package_next == (apm::FPackage*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 900        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.package) & (_db.ind_package_buckets_n - 1);
 901        apm::FPackage* *prev = &_db.ind_package_buckets_elems[index];
 902        do {
 903            apm::FPackage* ret = *prev;
 904            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 905                break;
 906            }
 907            if ((*ret).package == row.package) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 908                retval = false;
 909                break;
 910            }
 911            prev = &ret->ind_package_next;
 912        } while (true);
 913        if (retval) {
 914            row.ind_package_next = *prev;
 915            _db.ind_package_n++;
 916            *prev = &row;
 917        }
 918    }
 919    return retval;
 920}
 921
 922// --- apm.FDb.ind_package.Remove
 923// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 924void apm::ind_package_Remove(apm::FPackage& row) {
 925    if (LIKELY(row.ind_package_next != (apm::FPackage*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 926        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.package) & (_db.ind_package_buckets_n - 1);
 927        apm::FPackage* *prev = &_db.ind_package_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 928        while (apm::FPackage *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 929            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 930                *prev = next->ind_package_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 931                _db.ind_package_n--;
 932                row.ind_package_next = (apm::FPackage*)-1;// not-in-hash
 933                break;
 934            }
 935            prev = &next->ind_package_next;
 936        }
 937    }
 938}
 939
 940// --- apm.FDb.ind_package.Reserve
 941// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 942void apm::ind_package_Reserve(int n) {
 943    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_package_buckets_n;
 944    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_package_n + n;
 945    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 946    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 947        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 948        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(apm::FPackage*);
 949        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(apm::FPackage*);
 950        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 951        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 952        apm::FPackage* *new_buckets = (apm::FPackage**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 953        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 954            FatalErrorExit("apm.out_of_memory  field:apm.FDb.ind_package");
 955        }
 956        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 957        // rehash all entries
 958        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_package_buckets_n; i++) {
 959            apm::FPackage* elem = _db.ind_package_buckets_elems[i];
 960            while (elem) {
 961                apm::FPackage &row        = *elem;
 962                apm::FPackage* next       = row.ind_package_next;
 963                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.package) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 964                row.ind_package_next     = new_buckets[index];
 965                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 966                elem               = next;
 967            }
 968        }
 969        // free old array
 970        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_package_buckets_elems, old_size);
 971        _db.ind_package_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 972        _db.ind_package_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 973    }
 974}

 997// --- apm.FDb.pkgkey.InsertMaybe
 998// Create new row from struct.
 999// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
1000apm::FPkgkey* apm::pkgkey_InsertMaybe(const dev::Pkgkey &value) {
1001    apm::FPkgkey *row = &pkgkey_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
1002    pkgkey_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dev::Pkgkey&>(value));
1003    bool ok = pkgkey_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
1004    if (!ok) {
1005        pkgkey_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
1006        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
1007    }
1008    return row;
1009}

1011// --- apm.FDb.pkgkey.AllocMem
1012// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
1013void* apm::pkgkey_AllocMem() {
1014    u64 new_nelems     = _db.pkgkey_n+1;
1015    // compute level and index on level
1016    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
1017    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
1018    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
1019    void *ret = NULL;
1020    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
1021    apm::FPkgkey*  lev   = NULL;
1022    if (bsr < 32) {
1023        lev = _db.pkgkey_lary[bsr];
1024        if (!lev) {
1025            lev=(apm::FPkgkey*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(apm::FPkgkey) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
1026            _db.pkgkey_lary[bsr] = lev;
1027        }
1028    }
1029    // allocate element from this level
1030    if (lev) {
1031        _db.pkgkey_n = i32(new_nelems);
1032        ret = lev + index;
1033    }
1034    return ret;
1035}

1037// --- apm.FDb.pkgkey.RemoveAll
1038// Remove all elements from Lary
1039void apm::pkgkey_RemoveAll() {
1040    for (u64 n = _db.pkgkey_n; n>0; ) {
1041        n--;
1042        pkgkey_qFind(u64(n)).~FPkgkey(); // destroy last element
1043        _db.pkgkey_n = i32(n);
1044    }
1045}

1047// --- apm.FDb.pkgkey.RemoveLast
1048// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
1049void apm::pkgkey_RemoveLast() {
1050    u64 n = _db.pkgkey_n;
1051    if (n > 0) {
1052        n -= 1;
1053        pkgkey_qFind(u64(n)).~FPkgkey();
1054        _db.pkgkey_n = i32(n);
1055    }
1056}

1060    bool retval = true;
1061    retval = pkgkey_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
1062    return retval;

1065// --- apm.FDb.pkgkey.XrefMaybe
1066// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
1067// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
1068bool apm::pkgkey_XrefMaybe(apm::FPkgkey &row) {
1069    bool retval = true;
1070    (void)row;
1071    apm::FPackage* p_package = apm::ind_package_Find(package_Get(row));
1072    if (UNLIKELY(!p_package)) {
1073        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.bad_xref  index:apm.FDb.ind_package" << Keyval("key", package_Get(row));
1074        return false;
1075    }
1076    // insert pkgkey into index zd_pkgkey
1077    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1078        zd_pkgkey_Insert(*p_package, row);
1079    }
1080    // insert pkgkey into index ind_pkgkey
1081    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1082        bool success = ind_pkgkey_InsertMaybe(row);
1083        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
1084            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
1085            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "apm.duplicate_key  xref:apm.FDb.ind_pkgkey"; // check for duplicate key
1086            return false;
1087        }
1088    }
1089    return retval;
1090}

1181// --- apm.FDb.pkgdep.XrefMaybe
1182// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
1183// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
1184bool apm::pkgdep_XrefMaybe(apm::FPkgdep &row) {
1185    bool retval = true;
1186    (void)row;
1187    apm::FPackage* p_parent = apm::ind_package_Find(parent_Get(row));
1188    if (UNLIKELY(!p_parent)) {
1189        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.bad_xref  index:apm.FDb.ind_package" << Keyval("key", parent_Get(row));
1190        return false;
1191    }
1192    // pkgdep: save pointer to parent
1193    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1194        row.p_parent = p_parent;
1195    }
1196    apm::FPackage* p_package = apm::ind_package_Find(package_Get(row));
1197    if (UNLIKELY(!p_package)) {
1198        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.bad_xref  index:apm.FDb.ind_package" << Keyval("key", package_Get(row));
1199        return false;
1200    }
1201    // pkgdep: save pointer to package
1202    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1203        row.p_package = p_package;
1204    }
1205    // insert pkgdep into index c_pkgdep
1206    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1207        c_pkgdep_Insert(*p_package, row);
1208    }
1209    // insert pkgdep into index c_pkgdep_parent
1210    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1211        c_pkgdep_parent_Insert(*p_parent, row);
1212    }
1213    return retval;
1214}

1302// --- apm.FDb.ind_mergefile.Find
1303// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
1304apm::FMergefile* apm::ind_mergefile_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
1305    u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_mergefile_buckets_n - 1);
1306    apm::FMergefile* *e = &_db.ind_mergefile_buckets_elems[index];
1307    apm::FMergefile* ret=NULL;
1308    do {
1309        ret       = *e;
1310        bool done = !ret || (*ret).mergefile == key;
1311        if (done) break;
1312        e         = &ret->ind_mergefile_next;
1313    } while (true);
1314    return ret;
1315}

1325// --- apm.FDb.ind_mergefile.GetOrCreate
1326// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
1327apm::FMergefile& apm::ind_mergefile_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
1328    apm::FMergefile* ret = ind_mergefile_Find(key);
1329    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
1330        ret         = &mergefile_Alloc();
1331        (*ret).mergefile = key;
1332        bool good = mergefile_XrefMaybe(*ret);
1333        if (!good) {
1334            mergefile_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
1335            ret = NULL;
1336        }
1337    }
1338    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "apm.create_error  table:ind_mergefile  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
1339    return *ret;
1340}

1342// --- apm.FDb.ind_mergefile.InsertMaybe
1343// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
1344bool apm::ind_mergefile_InsertMaybe(apm::FMergefile& row) {
1345    ind_mergefile_Reserve(1);
1346    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
1347    if (LIKELY(row.ind_mergefile_next == (apm::FMergefile*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1348        u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, row.mergefile) & (_db.ind_mergefile_buckets_n - 1);
1349        apm::FMergefile* *prev = &_db.ind_mergefile_buckets_elems[index];
1350        do {
1351            apm::FMergefile* ret = *prev;
1352            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
1353                break;
1354            }
1355            if ((*ret).mergefile == row.mergefile) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
1356                retval = false;
1357                break;
1358            }
1359            prev = &ret->ind_mergefile_next;
1360        } while (true);
1361        if (retval) {
1362            row.ind_mergefile_next = *prev;
1363            _db.ind_mergefile_n++;
1364            *prev = &row;
1365        }
1366    }
1367    return retval;
1368}
1369
1370// --- apm.FDb.ind_mergefile.Remove
1371// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
1372void apm::ind_mergefile_Remove(apm::FMergefile& row) {
1373    if (LIKELY(row.ind_mergefile_next != (apm::FMergefile*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1374        u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, row.mergefile) & (_db.ind_mergefile_buckets_n - 1);
1375        apm::FMergefile* *prev = &_db.ind_mergefile_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
1376        while (apm::FMergefile *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
1377            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
1378                *prev = next->ind_mergefile_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
1379                _db.ind_mergefile_n--;
1380                row.ind_mergefile_next = (apm::FMergefile*)-1;// not-in-hash
1381                break;
1382            }
1383            prev = &next->ind_mergefile_next;
1384        }
1385    }
1386}
1387
1388// --- apm.FDb.ind_mergefile.Reserve
1389// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
1390void apm::ind_mergefile_Reserve(int n) {
1391    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_mergefile_buckets_n;
1392    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_mergefile_n + n;
1393    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
1394    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
1395        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
1396        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(apm::FMergefile*);
1397        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(apm::FMergefile*);
1398        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
1399        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
1400        apm::FMergefile* *new_buckets = (apm::FMergefile**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
1401        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
1402            FatalErrorExit("apm.out_of_memory  field:apm.FDb.ind_mergefile");
1403        }
1404        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
1405        // rehash all entries
1406        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_mergefile_buckets_n; i++) {
1407            apm::FMergefile* elem = _db.ind_mergefile_buckets_elems[i];
1408            while (elem) {
1409                apm::FMergefile &row        = *elem;
1410                apm::FMergefile* next       = row.ind_mergefile_next;
1411                u32 index          = algo::cstring_Hash(0, row.mergefile) & (new_nbuckets-1);
1412                row.ind_mergefile_next     = new_buckets[index];
1413                new_buckets[index] = &row;
1414                elem               = next;
1415            }
1416        }
1417        // free old array
1418        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_mergefile_buckets_elems, old_size);
1419        _db.ind_mergefile_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
1420        _db.ind_mergefile_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
1421    }
1422}

1475// --- apm.FDb.ind_pkgkey.Remove
1476// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
1477void apm::ind_pkgkey_Remove(apm::FPkgkey& row) {
1478    if (LIKELY(row.ind_pkgkey_next != (apm::FPkgkey*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1479        u32 index = algo::Smallstr150_Hash(0, row.pkgkey) & (_db.ind_pkgkey_buckets_n - 1);
1480        apm::FPkgkey* *prev = &_db.ind_pkgkey_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
1481        while (apm::FPkgkey *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
1482            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
1483                *prev = next->ind_pkgkey_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
1484                _db.ind_pkgkey_n--;
1485                row.ind_pkgkey_next = (apm::FPkgkey*)-1;// not-in-hash
1486                break;
1487            }
1488            prev = &next->ind_pkgkey_next;
1489        }
1490    }
1491}
1492
1493// --- apm.FDb.ind_pkgkey.Reserve
1494// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
1495void apm::ind_pkgkey_Reserve(int n) {
1496    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_pkgkey_buckets_n;
1497    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_pkgkey_n + n;
1498    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
1499    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
1500        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
1501        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(apm::FPkgkey*);
1502        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(apm::FPkgkey*);
1503        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
1504        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
1505        apm::FPkgkey* *new_buckets = (apm::FPkgkey**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
1506        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
1507            FatalErrorExit("apm.out_of_memory  field:apm.FDb.ind_pkgkey");
1508        }
1509        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
1510        // rehash all entries
1511        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_pkgkey_buckets_n; i++) {
1512            apm::FPkgkey* elem = _db.ind_pkgkey_buckets_elems[i];
1513            while (elem) {
1514                apm::FPkgkey &row        = *elem;
1515                apm::FPkgkey* next       = row.ind_pkgkey_next;
1516                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr150_Hash(0, row.pkgkey) & (new_nbuckets-1);
1517                row.ind_pkgkey_next     = new_buckets[index];
1518                new_buckets[index] = &row;
1519                elem               = next;
1520            }
1521        }
1522        // free old array
1523        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_pkgkey_buckets_elems, old_size);
1524        _db.ind_pkgkey_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
1525        _db.ind_pkgkey_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
1526    }
1527}

1529// --- apm.FDb.ctype.Alloc
1530// Allocate memory for new default row.
1531// If out of memory, process is killed.
1532apm::FCtype& apm::ctype_Alloc() {
1533    apm::FCtype* row = ctype_AllocMaybe();
1534    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
1535        FatalErrorExit("apm.out_of_mem  field:apm.FDb.ctype  comment:'Alloc failed'");
1536    }

1540// --- apm.FDb.ctype.AllocMaybe
1541// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
1542apm::FCtype* apm::ctype_AllocMaybe() {
1543    apm::FCtype *row = (apm::FCtype*)ctype_AllocMem();
1544    if (row) {
1545        new (row) apm::FCtype; // call constructor
1546    }
1547    return row;
1548}

1550// --- apm.FDb.ctype.InsertMaybe
1551// Create new row from struct.
1552// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
1553apm::FCtype* apm::ctype_InsertMaybe(const dmmeta::Ctype &value) {
1554    apm::FCtype *row = &ctype_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
1555    ctype_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dmmeta::Ctype&>(value));
1556    bool ok = ctype_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
1557    if (!ok) {
1558        ctype_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
1559        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
1560    }
1561    return row;
1562}
1563
1564// --- apm.FDb.ctype.AllocMem
1565// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
1566void* apm::ctype_AllocMem() {
1567    u64 new_nelems     = _db.ctype_n+1;
1568    // compute level and index on level
1569    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
1570    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
1571    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
1572    void *ret = NULL;
1573    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
1574    apm::FCtype*  lev   = NULL;
1575    if (bsr < 32) {
1576        lev = _db.ctype_lary[bsr];
1577        if (!lev) {
1578            lev=(apm::FCtype*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(apm::FCtype) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
1579            _db.ctype_lary[bsr] = lev;
1580        }
1581    }
1582    // allocate element from this level
1583    if (lev) {
1584        _db.ctype_n = i32(new_nelems);
1585        ret = lev + index;
1586    }
1587    return ret;
1588}
1589
1590// --- apm.FDb.ctype.RemoveAll
1591// Remove all elements from Lary
1592void apm::ctype_RemoveAll() {
1593    for (u64 n = _db.ctype_n; n>0; ) {
1594        n--;
1595        ctype_qFind(u64(n)).~FCtype(); // destroy last element
1596        _db.ctype_n = i32(n);
1597    }
1598}
1599
1600// --- apm.FDb.ctype.RemoveLast
1601// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
1602void apm::ctype_RemoveLast() {
1603    u64 n = _db.ctype_n;
1604    if (n > 0) {
1605        n -= 1;
1606        ctype_qFind(u64(n)).~FCtype();
1607        _db.ctype_n = i32(n);
1608    }
1609}

1612static bool apm::ctype_InputMaybe(dmmeta::Ctype &elem) {
1613    bool retval = true;
1614    retval = ctype_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
1615    return retval;
1616}

1618// --- apm.FDb.ctype.XrefMaybe
1619// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
1620// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
1621bool apm::ctype_XrefMaybe(apm::FCtype &row) {
1622    bool retval = true;
1623    (void)row;
1624    // insert ctype into index ind_ctype
1625    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1626        bool success = ind_ctype_InsertMaybe(row);
1627        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
1628            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
1629            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "apm.duplicate_key  xref:apm.FDb.ind_ctype"; // check for duplicate key
1630            return false;
1631        }
1632    }
1633    return retval;
1634}

1636// --- apm.FDb.ind_ctype.Find
1637// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
1638apm::FCtype* apm::ind_ctype_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
1639    u32 index = algo::Smallstr100_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_ctype_buckets_n - 1);
1640    apm::FCtype* *e = &_db.ind_ctype_buckets_elems[index];
1641    apm::FCtype* ret=NULL;
1642    do {
1643        ret       = *e;
1644        bool done = !ret || (*ret).ctype == key;
1645        if (done) break;
1646        e         = &ret->ind_ctype_next;
1647    } while (true);
1648    return ret;
1649}

1651// --- apm.FDb.ind_ctype.FindX
1652// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
1653apm::FCtype& apm::ind_ctype_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
1654    apm::FCtype* ret = ind_ctype_Find(key);
1655    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "apm.key_error  table:ind_ctype  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
1656    return *ret;
1657}

1659// --- apm.FDb.ind_ctype.GetOrCreate
1660// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
1661apm::FCtype& apm::ind_ctype_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
1662    apm::FCtype* ret = ind_ctype_Find(key);
1663    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
1664        ret         = &ctype_Alloc();
1665        (*ret).ctype = key;
1666        bool good = ctype_XrefMaybe(*ret);
1667        if (!good) {
1668            ctype_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
1669            ret = NULL;
1670        }
1671    }
1672    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "apm.create_error  table:ind_ctype  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
1673    return *ret;
1674}

1676// --- apm.FDb.ind_ctype.InsertMaybe
1677// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
1678bool apm::ind_ctype_InsertMaybe(apm::FCtype& row) {
1679    ind_ctype_Reserve(1);
1680    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
1681    if (LIKELY(row.ind_ctype_next == (apm::FCtype*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1682        u32 index = algo::Smallstr100_Hash(0, row.ctype) & (_db.ind_ctype_buckets_n - 1);
1683        apm::FCtype* *prev = &_db.ind_ctype_buckets_elems[index];
1684        do {
1685            apm::FCtype* ret = *prev;
1686            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
1687                break;
1688            }
1689            if ((*ret).ctype == row.ctype) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
1690                retval = false;
1691                break;
1692            }
1693            prev = &ret->ind_ctype_next;
1694        } while (true);
1695        if (retval) {
1696            row.ind_ctype_next = *prev;
1697            _db.ind_ctype_n++;
1698            *prev = &row;
1699        }
1700    }
1701    return retval;
1702}

1847// --- apm.FDb.field.XrefMaybe
1848// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
1849// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
1850bool apm::field_XrefMaybe(apm::FField &row) {
1851    bool retval = true;
1852    (void)row;
1853    apm::FCtype* p_ctype = apm::ind_ctype_Find(ctype_Get(row));
1854    if (UNLIKELY(!p_ctype)) {
1855        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.bad_xref  index:apm.FDb.ind_ctype" << Keyval("key", ctype_Get(row));
1856        return false;
1857    }
1858    // field: save pointer to ctype
1859    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1860        row.p_ctype = p_ctype;
1861    }
1862    apm::FCtype* p_arg = apm::ind_ctype_Find(row.arg);
1863    if (UNLIKELY(!p_arg)) {
1864        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.bad_xref  index:apm.FDb.ind_ctype" << Keyval("key", row.arg);
1865        return false;
1866    }
1867    // field: save pointer to arg
1868    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1869        row.p_arg = p_arg;
1870    }
1871    // insert field into index ind_field
1872    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1873        bool success = ind_field_InsertMaybe(row);
1874        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
1875            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
1876            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "apm.duplicate_key  xref:apm.FDb.ind_field"; // check for duplicate key
1877            return false;
1878        }
1879    }
1880    // insert field into index c_field
1881    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1882        c_field_Insert(*p_ctype, row);
1883    }
1884    return retval;
1885}

1967        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway

1977                apm::FField &row        = *elem;
1978                apm::FField* next       = row.ind_field_next;
1979                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr100_Hash(0, row.field) & (new_nbuckets-1);
1980                row.ind_field_next     = new_buckets[index];
1981                new_buckets[index] = &row;
1982                elem               = next;
1983            }
1984        }
1985        // free old array
1986        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_field_buckets_elems, old_size);
1987        _db.ind_field_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
1988        _db.ind_field_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
1989    }
1990}

2013// --- apm.FDb.ssimfile.InsertMaybe
2014// Create new row from struct.
2015// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
2016apm::FSsimfile* apm::ssimfile_InsertMaybe(const dmmeta::Ssimfile &value) {
2017    apm::FSsimfile *row = &ssimfile_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
2018    ssimfile_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dmmeta::Ssimfile&>(value));
2019    bool ok = ssimfile_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
2020    if (!ok) {
2021        ssimfile_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
2022        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
2023    }
2024    return row;
2025}

2027// --- apm.FDb.ssimfile.AllocMem
2028// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
2029void* apm::ssimfile_AllocMem() {
2030    u64 new_nelems     = _db.ssimfile_n+1;
2031    // compute level and index on level
2032    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
2033    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
2034    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
2035    void *ret = NULL;
2036    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
2037    apm::FSsimfile*  lev   = NULL;
2038    if (bsr < 32) {
2039        lev = _db.ssimfile_lary[bsr];
2040        if (!lev) {
2041            lev=(apm::FSsimfile*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(apm::FSsimfile) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
2042            _db.ssimfile_lary[bsr] = lev;
2043        }
2044    }
2045    // allocate element from this level
2046    if (lev) {
2047        _db.ssimfile_n = i32(new_nelems);
2048        ret = lev + index;
2049    }
2050    return ret;
2051}
2052
2053// --- apm.FDb.ssimfile.RemoveAll
2054// Remove all elements from Lary
2055void apm::ssimfile_RemoveAll() {
2056    for (u64 n = _db.ssimfile_n; n>0; ) {
2057        n--;
2058        ssimfile_qFind(u64(n)).~FSsimfile(); // destroy last element
2059        _db.ssimfile_n = i32(n);
2060    }
2061}
2062
2063// --- apm.FDb.ssimfile.RemoveLast
2064// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
2065void apm::ssimfile_RemoveLast() {
2066    u64 n = _db.ssimfile_n;
2067    if (n > 0) {
2068        n -= 1;
2069        ssimfile_qFind(u64(n)).~FSsimfile();
2070        _db.ssimfile_n = i32(n);
2071    }
2072}

2081// --- apm.FDb.ssimfile.XrefMaybe
2082// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
2083// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
2084bool apm::ssimfile_XrefMaybe(apm::FSsimfile &row) {
2085    bool retval = true;
2086    (void)row;
2087    apm::FCtype* p_ctype = apm::ind_ctype_Find(row.ctype);
2088    if (UNLIKELY(!p_ctype)) {
2089        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.bad_xref  index:apm.FDb.ind_ctype" << Keyval("key", row.ctype);
2090        return false;
2091    }
2092    // ssimfile: save pointer to ctype
2093    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
2094        row.p_ctype = p_ctype;
2095    }
2096    // insert ssimfile into index ind_ssimfile
2097    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
2098        bool success = ind_ssimfile_InsertMaybe(row);
2099        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
2100            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
2101            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "apm.duplicate_key  xref:apm.FDb.ind_ssimfile"; // check for duplicate key
2102            return false;
2103        }
2104    }
2105    // insert ssimfile into index c_ssimfile
2106    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
2107        bool success = c_ssimfile_InsertMaybe(*p_ctype, row);
2108        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
2109            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
2110            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "apm.duplicate_key  xref:apm.FCtype.c_ssimfile"; // check for duplicate key
2111            return false;
2112        }
2113    }
2114    return retval;
2115}

2117// --- apm.FDb.ind_ssimfile.Find
2118// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
2119apm::FSsimfile* apm::ind_ssimfile_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
2120    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_ssimfile_buckets_n - 1);
2121    apm::FSsimfile* *e = &_db.ind_ssimfile_buckets_elems[index];
2122    apm::FSsimfile* ret=NULL;
2123    do {
2124        ret       = *e;
2125        bool done = !ret || (*ret).ssimfile == key;
2126        if (done) break;
2127        e         = &ret->ind_ssimfile_next;
2128    } while (true);
2129    return ret;
2130}

2140// --- apm.FDb.ind_ssimfile.InsertMaybe
2141// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
2142bool apm::ind_ssimfile_InsertMaybe(apm::FSsimfile& row) {
2143    ind_ssimfile_Reserve(1);
2144    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
2145    if (LIKELY(row.ind_ssimfile_next == (apm::FSsimfile*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2146        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.ssimfile) & (_db.ind_ssimfile_buckets_n - 1);
2147        apm::FSsimfile* *prev = &_db.ind_ssimfile_buckets_elems[index];
2148        do {
2149            apm::FSsimfile* ret = *prev;
2150            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
2151                break;
2152            }
2153            if ((*ret).ssimfile == row.ssimfile) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
2154                retval = false;
2155                break;
2156            }
2157            prev = &ret->ind_ssimfile_next;
2158        } while (true);
2159        if (retval) {
2160            row.ind_ssimfile_next = *prev;
2161            _db.ind_ssimfile_n++;
2162            *prev = &row;
2163        }
2164    }
2165    return retval;
2166}

2168// --- apm.FDb.ind_ssimfile.Remove
2169// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
2170void apm::ind_ssimfile_Remove(apm::FSsimfile& row) {
2171    if (LIKELY(row.ind_ssimfile_next != (apm::FSsimfile*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2172        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.ssimfile) & (_db.ind_ssimfile_buckets_n - 1);
2173        apm::FSsimfile* *prev = &_db.ind_ssimfile_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
2174        while (apm::FSsimfile *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
2175            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
2176                *prev = next->ind_ssimfile_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
2177                _db.ind_ssimfile_n--;
2178                row.ind_ssimfile_next = (apm::FSsimfile*)-1;// not-in-hash
2179                break;
2180            }
2181            prev = &next->ind_ssimfile_next;
2182        }
2183    }
2184}

2186// --- apm.FDb.ind_ssimfile.Reserve
2187// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
2188void apm::ind_ssimfile_Reserve(int n) {
2189    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_ssimfile_buckets_n;
2190    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_ssimfile_n + n;
2191    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
2192    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
2193        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
2194        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(apm::FSsimfile*);
2195        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(apm::FSsimfile*);
2196        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
2197        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
2198        apm::FSsimfile* *new_buckets = (apm::FSsimfile**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
2199        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
2200            FatalErrorExit("apm.out_of_memory  field:apm.FDb.ind_ssimfile");
2201        }
2202        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
2203        // rehash all entries
2204        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_ssimfile_buckets_n; i++) {
2205            apm::FSsimfile* elem = _db.ind_ssimfile_buckets_elems[i];
2206            while (elem) {
2207                apm::FSsimfile &row        = *elem;
2208                apm::FSsimfile* next       = row.ind_ssimfile_next;
2209                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.ssimfile) & (new_nbuckets-1);
2210                row.ind_ssimfile_next     = new_buckets[index];
2211                new_buckets[index] = &row;
2212                elem               = next;
2213            }
2214        }
2215        // free old array
2216        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_ssimfile_buckets_elems, old_size);
2217        _db.ind_ssimfile_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
2218        _db.ind_ssimfile_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
2219    }
2220}

2275// --- apm.FDb.rec.Reserve
2276// Preallocate memory for N more elements
2277// Return number of elements actually reserved.
2278u64 apm::rec_Reserve(u64 n_elems) {
2279    u64 ret = 0;
2280    while (ret < n_elems) {
2281        u64 size = _db.rec_blocksize; // underlying allocator is probably Lpool
2282        u64 reserved = rec_ReserveMem(size);
2283        ret += reserved;
2284        if (reserved == 0) {
2285            break;
2286        }
2287    }
2288    return ret;
2289}

2291// --- apm.FDb.rec.ReserveMem
2292// Allocate block of given size, break up into small elements and append to free list.
2293// Return number of elements reserved.
2294u64 apm::rec_ReserveMem(u64 size) {
2295    u64 ret = 0;
2296    if (size >= sizeof(apm::FRec)) {
2297        apm::FRec *mem = (apm::FRec*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(size);
2298        ret = mem ? size / sizeof(apm::FRec) : 0;
2299        // add newly allocated elements to the free list;
2300        for (u64 i=0; i < ret; i++) {
2301            mem[i].rec_next = _db.rec_free;
2302            _db.rec_free = mem+i;
2303        }
2304    }
2305    return ret;
2306}

2444// --- apm.FDb.zd_rec.Insert
2445// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
2446void apm::zd_rec_Insert(apm::FRec& row) {
2447    if (!zd_rec_InLlistQ(row)) {
2448        apm::FRec* old_tail = _db.zd_rec_tail;
2449        row.zd_rec_next = NULL;
2450        row.zd_rec_prev = old_tail;
2451        _db.zd_rec_tail = &row;
2452        apm::FRec **new_row_a = &old_tail->zd_rec_next;
2453        apm::FRec **new_row_b = &_db.zd_rec_head;
2454        apm::FRec **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
2455        *new_row = &row;
2456        _db.zd_rec_n++;
2457    }
2458}

2460// --- apm.FDb.zd_rec.Remove
2461// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
2462void apm::zd_rec_Remove(apm::FRec& row) {
2463    if (zd_rec_InLlistQ(row)) {
2464        apm::FRec* old_head       = _db.zd_rec_head;
2465        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
2466        apm::FRec* prev = row.zd_rec_prev;
2467        apm::FRec* next = row.zd_rec_next;
2468        // if element is first, adjust list head; otherwise, adjust previous element's next
2469        apm::FRec **new_next_a = &prev->zd_rec_next;
2470        apm::FRec **new_next_b = &_db.zd_rec_head;
2471        apm::FRec **new_next = prev ? new_next_a : new_next_b;
2472        *new_next = next;
2473        // if element is last, adjust list tail; otherwise, adjust next element's prev
2474        apm::FRec **new_prev_a = &next->zd_rec_prev;
2475        apm::FRec **new_prev_b = &_db.zd_rec_tail;

2660// --- apm.FDb.substr.Alloc
2661// Allocate memory for new default row.
2662// If out of memory, process is killed.
2663apm::FSubstr& apm::substr_Alloc() {
2664    apm::FSubstr* row = substr_AllocMaybe();
2665    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
2666        FatalErrorExit("apm.out_of_mem  field:apm.FDb.substr  comment:'Alloc failed'");
2667    }
2668    return *row;
2669}

2671// --- apm.FDb.substr.AllocMaybe
2672// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
2673apm::FSubstr* apm::substr_AllocMaybe() {
2674    apm::FSubstr *row = (apm::FSubstr*)substr_AllocMem();
2675    if (row) {
2676        new (row) apm::FSubstr; // call constructor
2677    }
2678    return row;
2679}
2680
2681// --- apm.FDb.substr.InsertMaybe
2682// Create new row from struct.
2683// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
2684apm::FSubstr* apm::substr_InsertMaybe(const dmmeta::Substr &value) {
2685    apm::FSubstr *row = &substr_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
2686    substr_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dmmeta::Substr&>(value));
2687    bool ok = substr_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
2688    if (!ok) {
2689        substr_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
2690        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
2691    }
2692    return row;
2693}
2694
2695// --- apm.FDb.substr.AllocMem
2696// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
2697void* apm::substr_AllocMem() {
2698    u64 new_nelems     = _db.substr_n+1;
2699    // compute level and index on level
2700    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
2701    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
2702    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
2703    void *ret = NULL;
2704    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
2705    apm::FSubstr*  lev   = NULL;
2706    if (bsr < 32) {
2707        lev = _db.substr_lary[bsr];
2708        if (!lev) {
2709            lev=(apm::FSubstr*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(apm::FSubstr) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
2710            _db.substr_lary[bsr] = lev;
2711        }
2712    }
2713    // allocate element from this level
2714    if (lev) {
2715        _db.substr_n = i32(new_nelems);
2716        ret = lev + index;
2717    }
2718    return ret;
2719}
2720
2721// --- apm.FDb.substr.RemoveAll
2722// Remove all elements from Lary
2723void apm::substr_RemoveAll() {
2724    for (u64 n = _db.substr_n; n>0; ) {
2725        n--;
2726        substr_qFind(u64(n)).~FSubstr(); // destroy last element
2727        _db.substr_n = i32(n);
2728    }
2729}
2730
2731// --- apm.FDb.substr.RemoveLast
2732// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
2733void apm::substr_RemoveLast() {
2734    u64 n = _db.substr_n;
2735    if (n > 0) {
2736        n -= 1;
2737        substr_qFind(u64(n)).~FSubstr();
2738        _db.substr_n = i32(n);
2739    }
2740}
2741
2742// --- apm.FDb.substr.InputMaybe
2743static bool apm::substr_InputMaybe(dmmeta::Substr &elem) {
2744    bool retval = true;
2745    retval = substr_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
2746    return retval;
2747}

2749// --- apm.FDb.substr.XrefMaybe
2750// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
2751// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
2752bool apm::substr_XrefMaybe(apm::FSubstr &row) {
2753    bool retval = true;
2754    (void)row;
2755    apm::FField* p_srcfield = apm::ind_field_Find(row.srcfield);
2756    if (UNLIKELY(!p_srcfield)) {
2757        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.bad_xref  index:apm.FDb.ind_field" << Keyval("key", row.srcfield);
2758        return false;
2759    }
2760    // substr: save pointer to srcfield
2761    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
2762        row.p_srcfield = p_srcfield;
2763    }
2764    apm::FField* p_field = apm::ind_field_Find(row.field);
2765    if (UNLIKELY(!p_field)) {
2766        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.bad_xref  index:apm.FDb.ind_field" << Keyval("key", row.field);
2767        return false;
2768    }
2769    // insert substr into index c_substr
2770    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
2771        bool success = c_substr_InsertMaybe(*p_field, row);
2772        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
2773            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
2774            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "apm.duplicate_key  xref:apm.FField.c_substr"; // check for duplicate key
2775            return false;
2776        }
2777    }
2778    return retval;
2779}

2809// --- apm.FDb.pkgrec.AllocMem
2810// Allocate space for one element
2811// If no memory available, return NULL.
2812void* apm::pkgrec_AllocMem() {
2813    apm::FPkgrec *row = _db.pkgrec_free;
2814    if (UNLIKELY(!row)) {
2815        pkgrec_Reserve(1);
2816        row = _db.pkgrec_free;
2817    }
2818    if (row) {
2819        _db.pkgrec_free = row->pkgrec_next;
2820    }
2821    return row;
2822}

2824// --- apm.FDb.pkgrec.FreeMem
2825// Remove mem from all global and cross indices, then deallocate mem
2826void apm::pkgrec_FreeMem(apm::FPkgrec &row) {
2827    if (UNLIKELY(row.pkgrec_next != (apm::FPkgrec*)-1)) {
2828        FatalErrorExit("apm.tpool_double_delete  pool:apm.FDb.pkgrec  comment:'double deletion caught'");
2829    }
2830    row.pkgrec_next = _db.pkgrec_free; // insert into free list
2831    _db.pkgrec_free  = &row;
2832}
2833
2834// --- apm.FDb.pkgrec.Reserve
2835// Preallocate memory for N more elements
2836// Return number of elements actually reserved.
2837u64 apm::pkgrec_Reserve(u64 n_elems) {
2838    u64 ret = 0;
2839    while (ret < n_elems) {
2840        u64 size = _db.pkgrec_blocksize; // underlying allocator is probably Lpool
2841        u64 reserved = pkgrec_ReserveMem(size);
2842        ret += reserved;
2843        if (reserved == 0) {
2844            break;
2845        }
2846    }
2847    return ret;
2848}
2849
2850// --- apm.FDb.pkgrec.ReserveMem
2851// Allocate block of given size, break up into small elements and append to free list.
2852// Return number of elements reserved.
2853u64 apm::pkgrec_ReserveMem(u64 size) {
2854    u64 ret = 0;
2855    if (size >= sizeof(apm::FPkgrec)) {
2856        apm::FPkgrec *mem = (apm::FPkgrec*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(size);
2857        ret = mem ? size / sizeof(apm::FPkgrec) : 0;
2858        // add newly allocated elements to the free list;
2859        for (u64 i=0; i < ret; i++) {
2860            mem[i].pkgrec_next = _db.pkgrec_free;
2861            _db.pkgrec_free = mem+i;
2862        }
2863    }
2864    return ret;
2865}

2867// --- apm.FDb.pkgrec.XrefMaybe
2868// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
2869// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
2870bool apm::pkgrec_XrefMaybe(apm::FPkgrec &row) {
2871    bool retval = true;
2872    (void)row;
2873    apm::FPackage* p_p_package = row.p_package;
2874    if (UNLIKELY(!p_p_package)) {
2875        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.null_ref  xref:apm.FPackage.zd_pkgrec";
2876        return false;
2877    }
2878    // insert pkgrec into index zd_pkgrec
2879    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
2880        zd_pkgrec_Insert(*p_p_package, row);
2881    }
2882    apm::FRec* p_p_rec = row.p_rec;
2883    if (UNLIKELY(!p_p_rec)) {
2884        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.null_ref  xref:apm.FRec.zd_rec_pkgrec";
2885        return false;
2886    }
2887    // insert pkgrec into index zd_rec_pkgrec
2888    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
2889        zd_rec_pkgrec_Insert(*p_p_rec, row);
2890    }
2891    apm::FPkgkey* p_p_pkgkey = row.p_pkgkey;
2892    if (UNLIKELY(!p_p_pkgkey)) {
2893        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.null_ref  xref:apm.FPkgkey.c_pkgrec";
2894        return false;
2895    }
2896    // insert pkgrec into index c_pkgrec
2897    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
2898        c_pkgrec_Insert(*p_p_pkgkey, row);
2899    }
2900    return retval;
2901}

3010// --- apm.FDb.ssimreq.AllocMem
3011// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
3012void* apm::ssimreq_AllocMem() {
3013    u64 new_nelems     = _db.ssimreq_n+1;
3014    // compute level and index on level
3015    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
3016    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
3017    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
3018    void *ret = NULL;
3019    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
3020    apm::FSsimreq*  lev   = NULL;
3021    if (bsr < 32) {
3022        lev = _db.ssimreq_lary[bsr];
3023        if (!lev) {
3024            lev=(apm::FSsimreq*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(apm::FSsimreq) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
3025            _db.ssimreq_lary[bsr] = lev;
3026        }
3027    }
3028    // allocate element from this level
3029    if (lev) {
3030        _db.ssimreq_n = i32(new_nelems);
3031        ret = lev + index;
3032    }
3033    return ret;
3034}

3064// --- apm.FDb.ssimreq.XrefMaybe
3065// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
3066// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
3067bool apm::ssimreq_XrefMaybe(apm::FSsimreq &row) {
3068    bool retval = true;
3069    (void)row;
3070    apm::FSsimfile* p_child_ssimfile = apm::ind_ssimfile_Find(child_ssimfile_Get(row));
3071    if (UNLIKELY(!p_child_ssimfile)) {
3072        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.bad_xref  index:apm.FDb.ind_ssimfile" << Keyval("key", child_ssimfile_Get(row));
3073        return false;
3074    }
3075    // ssimreq: save pointer to child_ssimfile
3076    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
3077        row.p_child_ssimfile = p_child_ssimfile;
3078    }
3079    apm::FCtype* p_parent_ctype = apm::ind_ctype_Find(parent_ctype_Get(row));
3080    if (UNLIKELY(!p_parent_ctype)) {
3081        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.bad_xref  index:apm.FDb.ind_ctype" << Keyval("key", parent_ctype_Get(row));
3082        return false;
3083    }
3084    // ssimreq: save pointer to parent_ctype
3085    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
3086        row.p_ctype = p_parent_ctype;
3087    }
3088    apm::FField* p_parent_field = apm::ind_field_Find(parent_field_Get(row));
3089    if (UNLIKELY(!p_parent_field)) {
3090        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "apm.bad_xref  index:apm.FDb.ind_field" << Keyval("key", parent_field_Get(row));
3091        return false;
3092    }
3093    // ssimreq: save pointer to parent_field
3094    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
3095        row.p_field = p_parent_field;
3096    }
3097    // insert ssimreq into index c_ssimreq
3098    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
3099        c_ssimreq_Insert(*p_parent_ctype, row);
3100    }
3101    return retval;
3102}

3190// --- apm.FDb.ind_mkdir.Find
3191// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
3192apm::FMkdir* apm::ind_mkdir_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
3193    u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_mkdir_buckets_n - 1);
3194    apm::FMkdir* *e = &_db.ind_mkdir_buckets_elems[index];
3195    apm::FMkdir* ret=NULL;
3196    do {
3197        ret       = *e;
3198        bool done = !ret || (*ret).mkdir == key;
3199        if (done) break;
3200        e         = &ret->ind_mkdir_next;
3201    } while (true);
3202    return ret;
3203}

3213// --- apm.FDb.ind_mkdir.GetOrCreate
3214// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
3215apm::FMkdir& apm::ind_mkdir_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
3216    apm::FMkdir* ret = ind_mkdir_Find(key);
3217    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
3218        ret         = &mkdir_Alloc();

3221        if (!good) {
3222            mkdir_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
3223            ret = NULL;
3224        }
3225    }
3226    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "apm.create_error  table:ind_mkdir  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
3227    return *ret;

3230// --- apm.FDb.ind_mkdir.InsertMaybe
3231// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
3232bool apm::ind_mkdir_InsertMaybe(apm::FMkdir& row) {
3233    ind_mkdir_Reserve(1);
3234    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
3235    if (LIKELY(row.ind_mkdir_next == (apm::FMkdir*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
3236        u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, row.mkdir) & (_db.ind_mkdir_buckets_n - 1);
3237        apm::FMkdir* *prev = &_db.ind_mkdir_buckets_elems[index];
3238        do {
3239            apm::FMkdir* ret = *prev;
3240            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
3241                break;
3242            }
3243            if ((*ret).mkdir == row.mkdir) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
3244                retval = false;
3245                break;
3246            }
3247            prev = &ret->ind_mkdir_next;
3248        } while (true);
3249        if (retval) {
3250            row.ind_mkdir_next = *prev;
3251            _db.ind_mkdir_n++;
3252            *prev = &row;
3253        }
3254    }
3255    return retval;
3256}
3257
3258// --- apm.FDb.ind_mkdir.Remove
3259// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
3260void apm::ind_mkdir_Remove(apm::FMkdir& row) {
3261    if (LIKELY(row.ind_mkdir_next != (apm::FMkdir*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
3262        u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, row.mkdir) & (_db.ind_mkdir_buckets_n - 1);
3263        apm::FMkdir* *prev = &_db.ind_mkdir_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
3264        while (apm::FMkdir *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
3265            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
3266                *prev = next->ind_mkdir_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
3267                _db.ind_mkdir_n--;
3268                row.ind_mkdir_next = (apm::FMkdir*)-1;// not-in-hash
3269                break;
3270            }
3271            prev = &next->ind_mkdir_next;
3272        }
3273    }
3274}
3275
3276// --- apm.FDb.ind_mkdir.Reserve
3277// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
3278void apm::ind_mkdir_Reserve(int n) {
3279    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_mkdir_buckets_n;
3280    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_mkdir_n + n;
3281    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
3282    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
3283        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
3284        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(apm::FMkdir*);
3285        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(apm::FMkdir*);
3286        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
3287        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
3288        apm::FMkdir* *new_buckets = (apm::FMkdir**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
3289        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
3290            FatalErrorExit("apm.out_of_memory  field:apm.FDb.ind_mkdir");
3291        }
3292        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
3293        // rehash all entries
3294        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_mkdir_buckets_n; i++) {
3295            apm::FMkdir* elem = _db.ind_mkdir_buckets_elems[i];
3296            while (elem) {
3297                apm::FMkdir &row        = *elem;
3298                apm::FMkdir* next       = row.ind_mkdir_next;
3299                u32 index          = algo::cstring_Hash(0, row.mkdir) & (new_nbuckets-1);
3300                row.ind_mkdir_next     = new_buckets[index];
3301                new_buckets[index] = &row;
3302                elem               = next;
3303            }
3304        }
3305        // free old array
3306        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_mkdir_buckets_elems, old_size);
3307        _db.ind_mkdir_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
3308        _db.ind_mkdir_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
3309    }
3310}
