3422// --- apm.FDb..Init
3423// Set all fields to initial values.
3424void apm::FDb_Init() {
3425    // initialize LAry package (apm.FDb.package)
3426    _db.package_n = 0;
3427    memset(_db.package_lary, 0, sizeof(_db.package_lary)); // zero out all level pointers
3428    apm::FPackage* package_first = (apm::FPackage*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(apm::FPackage) * (u64(1)<<4));
3429    if (!package_first) {
3430        FatalErrorExit("out of memory");
3431    }
3432    for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
3433        _db.package_lary[i]  = package_first;
3434        package_first    += 1ULL<<i;
3435    }
3436    _db.zd_sel_package_head = NULL; // (apm.FDb.zd_sel_package)
3437    _db.zd_sel_package_n = 0; // (apm.FDb.zd_sel_package)
3438    _db.zd_sel_package_tail = NULL; // (apm.FDb.zd_sel_package)
3439    // initialize hash table for apm::FPackage;
3440    _db.ind_package_n             	= 0; // (apm.FDb.ind_package)
3441    _db.ind_package_buckets_n     	= 4; // (apm.FDb.ind_package)
3442    _db.ind_package_buckets_elems 	= (apm::FPackage**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(apm::FPackage*)*_db.ind_package_buckets_n); // initial buckets (apm.FDb.ind_package)
3443    if (!_db.ind_package_buckets_elems) {
3444        FatalErrorExit("out of memory"); // (apm.FDb.ind_package)
3445    }
3446    memset(_db.ind_package_buckets_elems, 0, sizeof(apm::FPackage*)*_db.ind_package_buckets_n); // (apm.FDb.ind_package)
3447    // initialize LAry pkgkey (apm.FDb.pkgkey)
3448    _db.pkgkey_n = 0;
3449    memset(_db.pkgkey_lary, 0, sizeof(_db.pkgkey_lary)); // zero out all level pointers
3450    apm::FPkgkey* pkgkey_first = (apm::FPkgkey*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(apm::FPkgkey) * (u64(1)<<4));
3451    if (!pkgkey_first) {
3452        FatalErrorExit("out of memory");
3453    }
3454    for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
3455        _db.pkgkey_lary[i]  = pkgkey_first;
3456        pkgkey_first    += 1ULL<<i;
3457    }
3458    // initialize LAry pkgdep (apm.FDb.pkgdep)
3459    _db.pkgdep_n = 0;
3460    memset(_db.pkgdep_lary, 0, sizeof(_db.pkgdep_lary)); // zero out all level pointers
3461    apm::FPkgdep* pkgdep_first = (apm::FPkgdep*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(apm::FPkgdep) * (u64(1)<<4));
3462    if (!pkgdep_first) {
3463        FatalErrorExit("out of memory");
3464    }
3465    for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
3466        _db.pkgdep_lary[i]  = pkgdep_first;
3467        pkgdep_first    += 1ULL<<i;
3468    }
3469    // initialize LAry mergefile (apm.FDb.mergefile)
3470    _db.mergefile_n = 0;
3471    memset(_db.mergefile_lary, 0, sizeof(_db.mergefile_lary)); // zero out all level pointers

3833// --- apm.FPackage.zd_pkgkey.Insert
3834// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
3835void apm::zd_pkgkey_Insert(apm::FPackage& package, apm::FPkgkey& row) {
3836    if (!zd_pkgkey_InLlistQ(row)) {
3837        apm::FPkgkey* old_tail = package.zd_pkgkey_tail;
3838        row.zd_pkgkey_next = NULL;
3839        row.zd_pkgkey_prev = old_tail;
3840        package.zd_pkgkey_tail = &row;
3841        apm::FPkgkey **new_row_a = &old_tail->zd_pkgkey_next;
3842        apm::FPkgkey **new_row_b = &package.zd_pkgkey_head;
3843        apm::FPkgkey **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
3844        *new_row = &row;
3845        package.zd_pkgkey_n++;
3846    }
3847}
3848
3849// --- apm.FPackage.zd_pkgkey.Remove
3850// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
3851void apm::zd_pkgkey_Remove(apm::FPackage& package, apm::FPkgkey& row) {
3852    if (zd_pkgkey_InLlistQ(row)) {
3853        apm::FPkgkey* old_head       = package.zd_pkgkey_head;
3854        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
3855        apm::FPkgkey* prev = row.zd_pkgkey_prev;
3856        apm::FPkgkey* next = row.zd_pkgkey_next;
3857        // if element is first, adjust list head; otherwise, adjust previous element's next
3858        apm::FPkgkey **new_next_a = &prev->zd_pkgkey_next;
3859        apm::FPkgkey **new_next_b = &package.zd_pkgkey_head;
3860        apm::FPkgkey **new_next = prev ? new_next_a : new_next_b;
3861        *new_next = next;
3862        // if element is last, adjust list tail; otherwise, adjust next element's prev
3863        apm::FPkgkey **new_prev_a = &next->zd_pkgkey_prev;
3864        apm::FPkgkey **new_prev_b = &package.zd_pkgkey_tail;
3865        apm::FPkgkey **new_prev = next ? new_prev_a : new_prev_b;
3866        *new_prev = prev;
3867        package.zd_pkgkey_n--;
3868        row.zd_pkgkey_next=(apm::FPkgkey*)-1; // not-in-list
3869    }
3870}
3871
3872// --- apm.FPackage.zd_pkgkey.RemoveAll
3873// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
3874void apm::zd_pkgkey_RemoveAll(apm::FPackage& package) {
3875    apm::FPkgkey* row = package.zd_pkgkey_head;
3876    package.zd_pkgkey_head = NULL;
3877    package.zd_pkgkey_tail = NULL;
3878    package.zd_pkgkey_n = 0;
3879    while (row) {
3880        apm::FPkgkey* row_next = row->zd_pkgkey_next;
3881        row->zd_pkgkey_next  = (apm::FPkgkey*)-1;
3882        row->zd_pkgkey_prev  = NULL;
3883        row = row_next;
3884    }
3885}
3886
3887// --- apm.FPackage.zd_pkgkey.RemoveFirst
3888// If linked list is empty, return NULL. Otherwise unlink and return pointer to first element.
3889apm::FPkgkey* apm::zd_pkgkey_RemoveFirst(apm::FPackage& package) {
3890    apm::FPkgkey *row = NULL;
3891    row = package.zd_pkgkey_head;
3892    if (row) {
3893        apm::FPkgkey *next = row->zd_pkgkey_next;
3894        package.zd_pkgkey_head = next;
3895        apm::FPkgkey **new_end_a = &next->zd_pkgkey_prev;
3896        apm::FPkgkey **new_end_b = &package.zd_pkgkey_tail;
3897        apm::FPkgkey **new_end = next ? new_end_a : new_end_b;
3898        *new_end = NULL;
3899        package.zd_pkgkey_n--;
3900        row->zd_pkgkey_next = (apm::FPkgkey*)-1; // mark as not-in-list
3901    }
3902    return row;
3903}

3905// --- apm.FPackage.c_pkgdep.Insert

3931// --- apm.FPackage.c_pkgdep.Remove
3932// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
3933void apm::c_pkgdep_Remove(apm::FPackage& package, apm::FPkgdep& row) {
3934    if (bool_Update(row.package_c_pkgdep_in_ary,false)) {
3935        int lim = package.c_pkgdep_n;
3936        apm::FPkgdep* *elems = package.c_pkgdep_elems;
3937        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
3938        // if found, shift array.
3939        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
3940            apm::FPkgdep* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
3941            if (elem == &row) {
3942                int j = i + 1;
3943                size_t nbytes = sizeof(apm::FPkgdep*) * (lim - j);
3944                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
3945                package.c_pkgdep_n = lim - 1;
3946                break;
3947            }
3948        }
3949    }
3950}

3952// --- apm.FPackage.c_pkgdep.Reserve
3953// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
3954void apm::c_pkgdep_Reserve(apm::FPackage& package, u32 n) {
3955    u32 old_max = package.c_pkgdep_max;
3956    if (UNLIKELY(package.c_pkgdep_n + n > old_max)) {
3957        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
3958        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(apm::FPkgdep*);
3959        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(apm::FPkgdep*);
3960        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(package.c_pkgdep_elems, old_size, new_size);
3961        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
3962            FatalErrorExit("apm.out_of_memory  field:apm.FPackage.c_pkgdep");
3963        }
3964        package.c_pkgdep_elems = (apm::FPkgdep**)new_mem;
3965        package.c_pkgdep_max = new_max;
3966    }
3967}

4033// --- apm.FPackage.zd_pkgrec.Insert
4034// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
4035void apm::zd_pkgrec_Insert(apm::FPackage& package, apm::FPkgrec& row) {
4036    if (!zd_pkgrec_InLlistQ(row)) {
4037        apm::FPkgrec* old_tail = package.zd_pkgrec_tail;
4038        row.zd_pkgrec_next = NULL;
4039        row.zd_pkgrec_prev = old_tail;
4040        package.zd_pkgrec_tail = &row;
4041        apm::FPkgrec **new_row_a = &old_tail->zd_pkgrec_next;
4042        apm::FPkgrec **new_row_b = &package.zd_pkgrec_head;
4043        apm::FPkgrec **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
4044        *new_row = &row;
4045        package.zd_pkgrec_n++;
4046    }
4047}
4048
4049// --- apm.FPackage.zd_pkgrec.Remove
4050// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
4051void apm::zd_pkgrec_Remove(apm::FPackage& package, apm::FPkgrec& row) {
4052    if (zd_pkgrec_InLlistQ(row)) {
4053        apm::FPkgrec* old_head       = package.zd_pkgrec_head;
4054        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
4055        apm::FPkgrec* prev = row.zd_pkgrec_prev;
4056        apm::FPkgrec* next = row.zd_pkgrec_next;
4057        // if element is first, adjust list head; otherwise, adjust previous element's next
4058        apm::FPkgrec **new_next_a = &prev->zd_pkgrec_next;
4059        apm::FPkgrec **new_next_b = &package.zd_pkgrec_head;
4060        apm::FPkgrec **new_next = prev ? new_next_a : new_next_b;
4061        *new_next = next;
4062        // if element is last, adjust list tail; otherwise, adjust next element's prev
4063        apm::FPkgrec **new_prev_a = &next->zd_pkgrec_prev;
4064        apm::FPkgrec **new_prev_b = &package.zd_pkgrec_tail;
4065        apm::FPkgrec **new_prev = next ? new_prev_a : new_prev_b;
4066        *new_prev = prev;
4067        package.zd_pkgrec_n--;
4068        row.zd_pkgrec_next=(apm::FPkgrec*)-1; // not-in-list
4069    }
4070}

4072// --- apm.FPackage.zd_pkgrec.RemoveAll
4073// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
4074void apm::zd_pkgrec_RemoveAll(apm::FPackage& package) {
4075    apm::FPkgrec* row = package.zd_pkgrec_head;
4076    package.zd_pkgrec_head = NULL;
4077    package.zd_pkgrec_tail = NULL;
4078    package.zd_pkgrec_n = 0;
4079    while (row) {
4080        apm::FPkgrec* row_next = row->zd_pkgrec_next;
4081        row->zd_pkgrec_next  = (apm::FPkgrec*)-1;
4082        row->zd_pkgrec_prev  = NULL;
4083        row = row_next;
4084    }
4085}

4087// --- apm.FPackage.zd_pkgrec.RemoveFirst
4088// If linked list is empty, return NULL. Otherwise unlink and return pointer to first element.
4089apm::FPkgrec* apm::zd_pkgrec_RemoveFirst(apm::FPackage& package) {
4090    apm::FPkgrec *row = NULL;
4091    row = package.zd_pkgrec_head;
4092    if (row) {
4093        apm::FPkgrec *next = row->zd_pkgrec_next;
4094        package.zd_pkgrec_head = next;
4095        apm::FPkgrec **new_end_a = &next->zd_pkgrec_prev;
4096        apm::FPkgrec **new_end_b = &package.zd_pkgrec_tail;
4097        apm::FPkgrec **new_end = next ? new_end_a : new_end_b;
4098        *new_end = NULL;
4099        package.zd_pkgrec_n--;
4100        row->zd_pkgrec_next = (apm::FPkgrec*)-1; // mark as not-in-list
4101    }
4102    return row;
4103}

4377// --- apm.FRec.zd_rec_pkgrec.Remove
4378// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
4379void apm::zd_rec_pkgrec_Remove(apm::FRec& rec, apm::FPkgrec& row) {
4380    if (zd_rec_pkgrec_InLlistQ(row)) {
4381        apm::FPkgrec* old_head       = rec.zd_rec_pkgrec_head;
4382        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
4383        apm::FPkgrec* prev = row.zd_rec_pkgrec_prev;
4384        apm::FPkgrec* next = row.zd_rec_pkgrec_next;
4385        // if element is first, adjust list head; otherwise, adjust previous element's next
4386        apm::FPkgrec **new_next_a = &prev->zd_rec_pkgrec_next;
4387        apm::FPkgrec **new_next_b = &rec.zd_rec_pkgrec_head;
4388        apm::FPkgrec **new_next = prev ? new_next_a : new_next_b;
4389        *new_next = next;
4390        // if element is last, adjust list tail; otherwise, adjust next element's prev
4391        apm::FPkgrec **new_prev_a = &next->zd_rec_pkgrec_prev;
4392        apm::FPkgrec **new_prev_b = &rec.zd_rec_pkgrec_tail;
4393        apm::FPkgrec **new_prev = next ? new_prev_a : new_prev_b;
4394        *new_prev = prev;
4395        rec.zd_rec_pkgrec_n--;
4396        row.zd_rec_pkgrec_next=(apm::FPkgrec*)-1; // not-in-list
4397    }

4492        apm::FRec **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
4493        *new_row = &row;

4495    }
4496}

4843            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
4844                case LE_STR8('d','m','m','e','t','a','.','S'): {
4845                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"ubstr",5)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,apm_TableId_dmmeta_Substr); ret = true; break; }
4846                    break;
4847                }
4848                case LE_STR8('d','m','m','e','t','a','.','s'): {
4849                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"ubstr",5)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,apm_TableId_dmmeta_substr); ret = true; break; }
4850                    break;
4851                }
4852            }
4853            break;
4854        }
4855        case 14: {
4856            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
4857                case LE_STR8('d','m','m','e','t','a','.','S'): {
4858                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"simreq",6)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,apm_TableId_dmmeta_Ssimreq); ret = true; break; }
4859                    break;
4860                }
4861                case LE_STR8('d','m','m','e','t','a','.','s'): {
4862                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"simreq",6)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,apm_TableId_dmmeta_ssimreq); ret = true; break; }
4863                    break;
4864                }
4865            }
4866            break;
4867        }
4868        case 15: {
4869            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
4870                case LE_STR8('d','m','m','e','t','a','.','S'): {
4871                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"simfile",7)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,apm_TableId_dmmeta_Ssimfile); ret = true; break; }
4872                    break;
4873                }
4874                case LE_STR8('d','m','m','e','t','a','.','s'): {
4875                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"simfile",7)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,apm_TableId_dmmeta_ssimfile); ret = true; break; }
4876                    break;
4877                }
4878            }
4879            break;
4880        }
4881    }
4882    return ret;
4883}

4885// --- apm.TableId.value.SetStrptr
4886// Convert string to field.
4887// If the string is invalid, set numeric value to DFLT
4888void apm::value_SetStrptr(apm::TableId& parent, algo::strptr rhs, apm_TableIdEnum dflt) {
4889    if (!value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs)) value_SetEnum(parent,dflt);
4890}
4891
4892// --- apm.TableId.value.ReadStrptrMaybe
4893// Convert string to field. Return success value
4894bool apm::value_ReadStrptrMaybe(apm::TableId& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
4895    bool retval = false;
4896    retval = value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs); // try symbol conversion
4897    if (!retval) { // didn't work? try reading as underlying type
4898        retval = i32_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.value,rhs);
4899    }
4900    return retval;
4901}
4902
4903// --- apm.TableId..ReadStrptrMaybe
4904// Read fields of apm::TableId from an ascii string.
4905// The format of the string is the format of the apm::TableId's only field
4906bool apm::TableId_ReadStrptrMaybe(apm::TableId &parent, algo::strptr in_str) {
4907    bool retval = true;
4908    retval = retval && value_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent, in_str);
4909    return retval;
4910}

4928// --- apm...main
4929int main(int argc, char **argv) {
4930    try {
4931        lib_json::FDb_Init();
4932        algo_lib::FDb_Init();
4933        lib_ctype::FDb_Init();
4934        lib_git::FDb_Init();
4935        apm::FDb_Init();
4936        algo_lib::_db.argc = argc;
4937        algo_lib::_db.argv = argv;
4938        algo_lib::IohookInit();
4939        apm::ReadArgv(); // dmmeta.main:apm
4940        apm::Main(); // user-defined main
4941    } catch(algo_lib::ErrorX &x) {
4942        prerr("apm.error  " << x); // there may be additional hints in DetachBadTags
4943        algo_lib::_db.exit_code = 1;
4944    }
4945    if (algo_lib::_db.last_signal) {
4946        algo_lib::_db.exit_code = 1;
4947    }
4948    try {
4949        apm::FDb_Uninit();
4950        lib_git::FDb_Uninit();
4951        lib_ctype::FDb_Uninit();
4952        algo_lib::FDb_Uninit();
4953        lib_json::FDb_Uninit();
4954    } catch(algo_lib::ErrorX &) {
4955        // don't print anything, might crash
4956        algo_lib::_db.exit_code = 1;
4957    }
4958    // only the lower 1 byte makes it to the outside world
4959    (void)i32_UpdateMin(algo_lib::_db.exit_code,255);
4960    return algo_lib::_db.exit_code;
4961}
